-- Saudi Earmarks $27 Billion for Road, Bridge Work, Riyadh Says
-- B y   D e e m a   A l m a s h a b i
-- 2012-09-24T07:46:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/saudi-earmarks-27-billion-for-road-bridge-work-riyadh-says.html
  Saudi Arabia  has allocated $27
billion to building roads and bridges in the next five years,
 al-Riyadh  reported, without saying where it got the information.  The kingdom is ranked second among Middle Eastern countries
in terms of infrastructure expenditure after the United Arab
Emirates, which is spending $58 billion on roads and bridges,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Deema Almashabi in Riyadh at 
 dalmashabi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
